      "date": "2017-04-08 01:40:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn lfs.1 lines 45 and 183, for lfs getstripe we have the –component-count flag and no argument after it:\n[\\fB--component-count\\fR]\n\nIn lfs.c, line 215, we have an (optional?) argument specified for –component-count:\n[--component-count[=comp_count]]\nand in line 2302, we have that there is no argument:\n\t{\"component-count\",\tno_argument, 0, LFS_COMP_COUNT_OPT},\n\nIf there is an optional argument for –component-count, then don’t we need to modify the lfs man page to reflect this?",
